to lose/to throw away/to discard/to cast away
to brandish (a figurative weapon, i.e. some measure intended to deal with the situation)/to resort to (some tactic)
to release/to set free/to allow (a person or an animal) to go/to liberate
hands tied and waiting to be captured
to take back (forcibly)/to recapture/to win back

to prevail/to achieve victory/to be victorious
